name: ABC
text: WATCH LIVE: We have the latest on the coronavirus pandemic after over 7,000 American lives were lost in the past week, according to ABC News' analysis of data from The COVID Tracking Project. https://t.co/MnbUUSuMRa

name: ABC
text: The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation announced it will commit an additional $70 million to make sure vaccines are available for everyone. https://t.co/Hasxi3zv4R

name: ABC
text: Paul Hornung, the dazzling “Golden Boy” of the Green Bay Packers whose singular ability to generate points as a runner, receiver, quarterback and kicker helped turn the team into an NFL dynasty, has died. He was 84. https://t.co/BEhmFSpzwf

name: ABC
text: "This is going to be the greatest drug distribution challenge that our country has ever faced because of the unique circumstances around the temperature requirement." https://t.co/t9B5PUTe7M

name: ABC
text: Dozens of Secret Service Uniformed Division officers are in isolation or quarantine due to testing positive for COVID-19 or having close contact with someone who is, a source familiar with the matter said. The majority are under quarantine as a precaution. https://t.co/klOpJnRQzU

name: ABC
text: FBI catches fugitive nearly 50 years after his escape from custody with new fingerprint technology. https://t.co/N13xbegMfm

name: ABC
text: A team of researchers have created a computer model that predicts how COVID-19 spreads in cities by studying anonymized cell phone data. Their findings indicate that most infections occur where people are in contact for long periods of time. https://t.co/NABax4mgIP
